\end{equation*}
$$

The transconductance can be adjusted by varying the control voltages, $\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{C} 1}$ and $\mathrm{V}_{\mathrm{C} 2}$, which are high-input impedance nodes and thus easily modifiable. It is important to note that, for this transconductor, matching is required only within the same type of transistors: n-channel transistors should match each other, and p-channel transistors should match each other, but there is no necessity for cross-matching between n- and p-channel transistors.
